dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: H. Liu
K. Simonyan
Y. Yang
dcterms:description: CIFAR-100 is a dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 100 classes, with 600 images per class. It is used for more fine-grained image classification tasks compared to CIFAR-10.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:description: ImageNet is a large visual database designed for use in visual object recognition software research. It contains over 1.2 million images labeled across 1,000 categories.
dcterms:title: ImageNet

dcterms:description: Randomly Labeled Real Data (RLRD) consists of real images from CIFAR-10 dataset with randomly assigned labels, used for exploring neural architecture search.
dcterms:title: Randomly Labeled Real Data (RLRD)

dcterms:description: Randomly Labeled Generative Data (RLGD) consists of generated images with randomly assigned labels, used for exploring neural architecture search.
dcterms:title: Randomly Labeled Generative Data (RLGD)

dcterms:description: Randomly Labeled Random Noise (RLRN) consists of random noise images with randomly assigned labels, used for exploring neural architecture search.
